                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/905a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. The Department i$ informed through the Peruvian Embassy here that Dr. Porras
                    has again postponed sailing and will leave April 26. The Department feels that
                    the delay caused in this manner would be very unfortunate, and the impression
                    created would be most undesirable, in view of the fact that the Chilean
                    delegation is already here. Inquire discreetly, therefore, as to whether it will
                    be <pb facs="0584" n="464" xml:id="pg_464"/> possible for the Peruvian
                    Government to instruct Dr. Porras to obtain an earlier sailing, or at least that
                    hi$ departure be not again postponed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
